    "The political theorist Ali Mazrui and Mazrui (1999) has studied the influence of English on African culture and argues that this influence changes the self-perceptions and social practices of African peoples.",
    "This need not be bad per se.",
    "Creole creates something new that we can greatly appreciate; cultural encounters can be enriching and broaden perspectives.",
    "The problem, then, is not cultural mixing and matching as such; on the contrary.",
    "Rather, it is the dominance of certain cultures over the others, that tends to be reflected or even perpetuated in AI language technology and which needs to be overcome if we are to promote epistemic justice."
  ],
